title: Do you think that BTS and BLACKPINK are on the same level? - Quora

response.answer_text: In my opinion, even though I AM somewhat a blink, BTS is on a whole other level. I will compare both groups in 8 different categories: Music, dance, concepts, performances, consistency, advertisement, personalities, and company Music BTS writes a lot of their music about their personal feelings and experiences as people with VERY deep and expressive lyrics that can be interpreted in multiple ways. They have a rich discography with dozens of songs and a lot of versatility and they have covered many different genres and each song is unique.  Blackpink’s music is VERY borderline and pretty all girl-crush and badass girl type music. While some of their songs are bops, they are hard to connect to because they weren’t written or produced by the girls and the songs all have similar meanings. Like they all have girl power vibes (nothing wrong with that but it gets repetitive after a while). Their lyrics are pretty straight-forward and their discography is so tiny. A lot of their songs are repetitive and have a similar formula, similar beats, and repetitive beats and concepts.  Choreography I feel like it’s a bit unfair to compare girl-group to boy-group choreography because, well, boy-group choreographies tend to be harder but I’ll compare anyway for the sake of this answer. BTS does not have the best choreography in the K-Pop industry but you have to admit it’s pretty good. And it’s more than just choreography. They put in so much power and energy and emotion into their dances that they make their choreographies look better and more extravagant than if someone else were to do the choreography.  Blackpink’s choreography is… okay. It’s nothing amazing or show-stopping and they’re pretty simple enough. But what I don’t like is how repetitive it is. A lot of the same dance moves are repeated frequently. Not only that, but sometimes, but the girls also don’t always have synchronization in some of their performances. And Lisa is such a good dancer but YG won’t let her shine with their choreography. Or more solos. And don’t get me started on the lazy Jennie scandal. I really want to defend Jennie but I don’t have any excuses for her actions.  Concepts BTS is one of the most experimental boy-groups in the industry. They have almost never repeat the same concept and show off their visuals in many different ways. Each comeback shows a new side of BTS that ARMYs love to see. Even each Map of The Soul, Love Yourself, and The Most Beautiful Moment in Life albums each had their own concept. From the Spring Day era to the ON Era, to the Blood, Sweat, and Tears Era, to the Not Today Era, and even the No More Dream Era. Each one is interesting and different. They experiment so much, it’s insane. I love how they don’t stick to one thing so, then, they attract all kinds of fans and people with different interests. From hip-hop to boy-crush to cute to sexy to practically every concept on the planet.  I find it kinda sad how little diversity there is in a lot of Blackpink’s concepts. They really all have the cute, badass girl vibe that I don’t mind but these girls are so beautiful so imagine how many concepts they could do and experiment with if their company just let them have a chance. The most unique concept that has stood out the most is As If It’s Your Last and that’s pretty much it/  Performances A lot of BTS’ performances are so fucking iconic and memorable. One of my favorites is IDOL when each member of the dance line got their own solo and that was when I just had to accept that BigHit is so iconic for making them do that. With Jimin’s serendipity when he’s in the bubble and when they performed IDOL, THE SEATS WERE LITERALLY SHAKING. And they barely even lip-sync. Jungkook and Jin’s vocals and J-Hope and RM’s rapping live are just so good and stable.  Some of Blackpink’s performances just feel SO underwhelming. I love how the girls sometimes don’t lip-sync but I really only like Jennie’s rap and Jisoo’s vocals. Yes, Lisa can rap and Rose can sing but not as well while performing sadly. When I watch their performances at award shows, I always just scroll to the comment section in boredom. It’s really just them and their choreographies that basically consist of them walking with a screen with colors in the background. SO boring.  Advertisement BTS and Blackpink advertise themselves and their comebacks VERY differently. BTS relies more on their personality as an advertisement for new fans and their comebacks with dozens and dozens of interviews. BigHit is smart with this because it shows to newer audiences the sense of humor and charisma that the boys have instead of your average boyband. They have done countless interviews with each comeback. Even if no one has even heard of the podcast or channel, they would still do the interview to advertise themselves.  While Blackpink does do interviews, I don’t think they do them as often and they do it with only big companies and channels. I feel like they rely more on fashion, makeup, and overall pretty big beauty brands to advertise themselves. I mean, Jennie has her own brand AND is the ambassador of Chanel. I feel like YG is smart for doing this. They rely on something that Blackpink definitely has: visuals. They probably have some of the most unique and best visuals in K-Pop and that’s how they advertise themselves. Pretty smart.  While BTS DOES do brand deals, they don’t do it as much as Blackpink and Blackpink mostly do it to show off their visuals. Personalities So this one may be a bit controversial so I’ll cut it short. One or two sentences from each member of each group. Jin has one of my favorite personalities in K-Pop because he has so much presence, charisma, and consistency. He knows how to make people laugh and smile. Suga doesn’t really care what people think so, most of the time, he doesn’t bother to put on a persona but that’s why so many fans are attracted to him and he’s so frequently biased. Hobi is such a ray of sweet sunshine and I know a lot of people find his persona cringy but I find it warm and cute. Namjoon just gives off big dad and intellectual vibes and he radiates the energy of a leader. Jimin is known for his sweet and childish personality and how naturally lovable he is. Taehyung is a very unpredictable, unique, eccentric, yet calm person and that is that attracts a lot of fans. Jungkook, as the most loved member, is very childish and playful who also can be a bit weird sometimes.  Jisoo is honestly one of my favorite members. She’s got a very soft and delicate personality and can also be a crackhead and she is one of the funniest female idols, in my opinion. I have mixed feelings about Jennie’s persona. She seems to care way too much about what other people think and her excessive aegyo can sometimes be annoying but she seems like a nice person with no malicious intent. I’m not really a big fan of Rose’s personality (personal preference) but she is the down-to-earth member, in my opinion. Other than that, I'm not that big of a fan. Lisa is my bias-wrecker because of her bubbly and childish personality that doesn’t come off as forced like Jennie’s. But her dance teacher mode is a bit scary.  Company The winner of this is just so obvious. BigHit is known to be one of the best companies in the K-Pop industry. No, it is not perfect but it is better than most. They let their idols have creative expression through music and choreography. They also lifted the dating ban (even if the members didn’t reveal their significant other or even have one). Not only that, diets may be encouraged but they are certainly not forced by the company. All the members’ diets were when they thought they needed to lose weight. They also really want to make fans happy by giving consistent comebacks and content. You never get bored. To add o, they only have Lee Hyun, TXT, and BTS so they could focus their time and energy on those three instead of having to worry about multiple groups all the time.  We all know the unfairness of YG with the mistreatment of 2ne1. Not only that, when Lisa was a trainee, but he also didn’t let anyone talk to her so she would learn Korean faster. Not gonna lie, that’s a bit messed up. And it’s so clear he picks favorites with Jennie outfits, solos, brand deals, and being the center and it’s so unfair to the other members. She got SO much hate for that. Also, why only one comeback a year for Blackpink and why no attention to your male groups?! And why doesn’t he defend or protect his idols??? Blinks had to pressure YG into protecting Lisa from death threats and where was he when it was Jennie VS the entire K-Pop fandom???  I’m so sorry, Blinks. I don’t hate Blackpink and I apologize for sounding so harsh but, biasing aside, I truly think BTS is the superior group. They have a bigger and more diverse discography, they have more respect from the K-Pop and the entertainment industry as a whole, they connect more with fans, their personalities feel more real, and they have more experience. I’m sorry but I need to give it to BTS. :)

response.answer_text: No they are not on the same level! Not even close! Music: The members of BTS are artists! Who are very involved and included in the process of making their own music! They are free to release their own solo music whenever they want. Of course BigHit has always a say in it but at the end of the day it‘s authentic. Their lyrics have so much depth and meaning! I would consider their music and music videos as art! The only thing they need is a real hit. A song EVERYBODY knows. Not only their fans. But that is hard, since it’s in korean. Also the structure of their songs usually is too complex. The girls from Blackpink are basically puppets and property of YG! They just sing what YG and the producers are telling them to sing! They only release things when the company want them to. BUT! I gotta say their music is a lot more catchy than BTS‘s songs! Simple structure, chorus usually in English so everybody can sing to it! Perfect! But also not really a lot meaning or true feelings behind it. Their songs are catchy….but also incredibly repetitive and all kinda sound the same. It’s showing of some girl power, swag and their stunning visuals. Success If you really wanna know how successful an act is: look how many physical albums and tickets they have sold. The amount of streams or the amount of awards doesn’t really give you a clue! Sure it’s nice and a pad on your shoulder. But does this really makes the money or shows you the amount of fans you really have? No! So this is all I’m saying: BTS sold out stadiums, arenas all over the world! They were constantly touring. Blackpink has not nearly sold as many tickets as BTS! It’s not even comparable! Also the amount of money BTS brought to the korean economy is not comparable to blackpink. BTS spoke at the UN, BTS got invited and performed at the Grammys and AMA‘s! I could go on and on

A Blink X ARMY here, so I’m gonna be objective and not cherry-picking either side. In terms of popularity, BTS IS ahead. If BTS popularity & influence both can score 9.9/10, BP prolly gets 9.5/10 for popularity and 6.9/10 for influence. BTS image is like a mix of boyfriend you never have + supporting guy bestfriends + flower boys image, so I get it when all the girls fall in love with them.+ their openess to their fans on cam and relatability is on another level that NOBODY can not touch yet, even BP. BlackPink is a mix of strong girl + rich hypebeast + glamour + elegant + queen-like image, basically a mix of beauty and bold.How the company produce the image—in itself—is very empowering to female audience. Espc with the rising of girl power movement & Equality-for-Asians-in-the-West-Entertainment-Industry movement, it’s kinda make BlackPink an icon for that in the eye of foreign Blinks, and even the Western entertainment media is portraying them like that on occasions. Yet, they’re not as close, nor as open as BTS does to their fans. And it’s understandable since the Big3 is famous for dictating their artists instead of letting them grow artistically and personally. This lack of openness is resulting in less score of BP’s influence in my opinion. In contrast, Bighit (The company which BTS is under) which considered to be “the noob” in the Kpop Industry (Well, not like noob-noob, but not that old either, compared to the Big 3. BTS is the very first artist the company debuted themselves) can be successful with BTS by breaking the typical “Big3 : Unwritten Ethical Code for Idols Attitude & Behaviour” somehow. That breaking-the-traditional-KPOP attitude is really good for BTS in developing their individual personality, creativity, and talent, or even simply being more honest on cam as an individual and a group. So, kudos to Bighit. If you follow them long enough, you can easily tell these differences by looking at all BTS vlogging videos. They have this unique bond and harmonious synergy as true friends, brothers, and family to each other (and not just company mates).On the top of all that, they’re also good at making instant connection with those people whom they’ve been working with (or being interviewed by), at least on cam, a thing that’s incomparable to any other group within the same batch just yet.

Honestly speaking, no they're not on the same level. Not at all. Bts is far ahead in terms of popularity and influence compared to Blackpink. And this holds true even when it comes to the work they they've done or are doing. I'm not belittling BP here. But they actually really aren't that popular. It's not that they don't have potential because they do. And they are really talented. I would say the fault lies with their agency here. They really need a good album. They actually went on a World Tour with so little songs which probably resulted in many of their tours not being so popular in the US. This isn't the case with Bts who have sold out tours every time. YG really needs to focus on BP and actually let them improve and develop their potential.

Hell to the moon and back, they are in NO way the same level. They can’t even be compared. LMAO. BTS is way way wayyy too far BP’s level. I’m sorry for all the blinks but, this is the truth. It’s the pill that is hard to swallow by lots of you. Not because your favs are known right now and is getting much hype (which somehow indeed happened with the help of BTS’ name in the industry), doesn’t mean they are in the same ground with Bangtan. Also, in my opinion, those girls are just overhyped, they aren’t even on the same level as 2ne1 even if they look like they’re trying to be like them. Hmmm

Sigh. This almost made a vein pop in my head… Much as it pains me to say this but bear with me a moment please… YG and Blinks need to stop spinning the image and actually allow Blackpink to realize what they lack and improve on it. They are good but they still have a long way to go. The moment they realize this is when they actually start growing. Instead of paying to make flowery write-ups, it would help a lot if they actually work on their harmony and maybe even participate in song writing workshops. Take away all the “prettyness” and all the hype right now, tell me what would be left of Blackpink? You have to understand that there are probably hundreds of trainees out there and groups that have left their families at a very young age and barely debuted and are working their asses off just to get a chance to even be noticed so if BP will just get everything handed to them, it is an insult to the whole KPop industry and also to BP. BP has very good potential and has already gotten their foot at the door. But if they continue to rely on media spins, I’m afraid they will have an expiry date pretty soon than any Blink would care to admit.

Just gonna say one thing. Three years in, bts had produced about 70 songs. (at LEAST write and produce legit every song) Three years in, black pink have produced like 15 songs . Maybe, it is because yg is a HORRIBLE COMPANY. But, I just don’t know if I could like a group that produces like only 5 songs a year so, in ways, bts are at a higher level. But, not as people or, a group, just in ways of production and reliability.

No. Not even on the same continent. I might not be so critical if BlackPink's last song Kill This Love wasn't a replica of 2NE1 and their music. YG has taken everything that was wonderful about 2NE1 and painted it all over BlackPink. Apparently it's working.

When it comes to influence and artistry, not even close. People like them for different reasons. BTS fans stay because of their artistry and personality whereas most of the BlackPink fans stan them bc of their visuals and yes, catchy songs that other people wrote for them. I saw lots of BP fans who unstan because they got sick of hearing same songs, beat and breakup lyrics over and over again.

Not at the moment, but their music is truly diverse. Plus, they still don’t have powerful fandom, that can rival Army. As for charisma and stage presence, I must say that they are equal. Plus they have been around for not even 3 years, so there is lot’s of room for improvement. BTS has double the experience, not to mention that they are boys, which means much more fangirls.

Just to be clear I'm an ARMY. Both groups are extremely talented and successful. There are many differences between the groups. However, I think overall they are on the same level when looking at how successful they are.
